1 _META <metadataxml><content><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;James Avery Thomas&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line /><line>&lt;tbody&gt;</line><line>&lt;tr&gt;</li
2 CONC ne><line>&lt;td valign="top"&gt;Birth:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/td&gt;</line><line>&lt;td align="left" valign="top"&gt;Oct. 31, 1812&lt;br&gt;Marengo County&lt;br&gt;Alabama, USA&lt;/td&gt;</line><line>&lt;/tr&gt;</line><line>&lt;tr&gt;</line><line>&lt;td val
2 CONC ign="top"&gt;Death:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/td&gt;</line><line>&lt;td align="left" valign="top"&gt;Apr. 28, 1865&lt;br&gt;Roans Prairie&lt;br&gt;Grimes County&lt;br&gt;Texas, USA&lt;/td&gt;</line><line>&lt;/tr&gt;</line><line>&lt;tr&gt;</line><line>&lt;td co
2 CONC lspan="2" valign="top"&gt;&lt;br&gt;Son of John Thomas and Phoebe Springer. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;JAMES AVERY THOMAS was born in Marengo County, Alabama in 1812. According to the 1850 and 1860 censuses, he was born in 1816 in TN or 1818 in GA. Perhap
2 CONC s he did not know himself. James came to Texas before 1835. At Montgomery County in 1842 he married *AMANDA WHEELER, daughter of *HENRY H. WHEELER and *MARY ANN SAWYER who were neighbors of the Thomas family in Alabama. It also appears that they we
2 CONC re neighbors in Georgia, all having arrived in Texas within a short time of each other. James and Amanda settled in Roans Prarie in Grimes County though at the time they first came there, Roans Prarie was in Montgomery County. James was a farmer. J
2 CONC ames died 28 Apr 1865 and is buried at Mustang Prarie. Amanda died 05 Sep 1896 at Mustang Prarie. The cemetery is located 100 yards from the Walker County line, 16 miles west of Huntsville, Texas, off Highway 30.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Jame
2 CONC s Thomas and Amanda Wheeler Thomas' Children born married died Phebe M 1853Willis Fulton John Henry1846Betty Thornton1928Sam 1862Sarah Jane Reed1888Archie 1860Mollie Coleman1945Mack 1857Jennie Thompson1937C. Dave1855Mallie McGilberry1942Katherine 1
2 CONC 850John Morris1938*Francis Marion1852*Susan Mullens1922&lt;br&gt;1850 Texas Census - Grimes County&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;James Thomas age 34 m TN &lt;br&gt;(he was born in GA, or AL not TN) &lt;br&gt;Amanda 24 f TN (she was born in GA) &lt;br&gt;Pheb
2 CONC e M. 7 f TX John 4 m TX &lt;br&gt;Samuel A. J. 2 m TX &lt;br&gt;Amanda C. J. 6/12 f TX &lt;br&gt;H. H. Wheeler 50 m NC &lt;br&gt;Mary Ann Wheeler 15 f AL (Granddaughter of Henry H. Wheeler)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;*JAMES and *AMANDA are listed as bein
2 CONC g unable to read or write. Their property is valued at $600. In the household is HENRY H. WHEELER, Amanda's father. Mary Ann Wheeler is Amanda's neice, daughter of her brother, John Wheeler. John lives two farms away from his sister Amanda with hi
2 CONC s wife Elizabeth and son Joseph Jr. but he denied paternity of the daughter living with Amanda. John listed his occupation as "none". Henry Wheeler's wife, Mary Ann Sawyer, does not appear on any census. &lt;br&gt; &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;1860 Texas Ce
2 CONC nsus-Bedias, Grimes County&lt;br&gt;J. Thomas 42 m GA farmer 480 - 700 &lt;br&gt;Amanda 31 f GA keeping house &lt;br&gt;Pheoby 17 f TX &lt;br&gt;John 14 m TX &lt;br&gt;Samuel 12 m TX &lt;br&gt;Catherine 10 f TX &lt;br&gt;Jane 8 f TX &lt;br&gt;Charl
2 CONC es 4 m TX &lt;br&gt;McGowan 2 m TX &lt;br&gt;Archie 9/12 m TX &lt;br&gt;Willis Fulton 21 m TX (he married Pheoby above) &lt;br&gt;Elizabeth Wheeler 35 f AL Insane, Pauper &lt;br&gt;Elizabeth Wheeler was the sister-in-law of Amanda. Amanda's brothe
2 CONC r John had her declared insane. James' real estate was worth $480 and his personal property was worth $700. Jane and McGowan do not appear on future censuses. Notice that Amanda lists her state of birth as GA. &lt;br&gt; &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;1870 Te
2 CONC xas Census - Grimes CountyAmanda Thomas 43 f GA &lt;br&gt;Marion 16 m TX &lt;br&gt;David 14 m TX &lt;br&gt;Sam 12 m TX &lt;br&gt;Archie 10 m TX&lt;br&gt;By the 1870 Census, James Avery had died, and *FRANCIS MARION THOMAS appears as the 16 year ol
2 CONC d Marion. For some reason, the dates in &lt;br&gt;the 1870 census are in error by two years for Amanda and Marion. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Note:&lt;br&gt;Some people say he is buried in Mustang Prairie.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Source: http://www.fortunecity
